items.text: Excellent food quality.... Loved their grilled puffer fish! Indoor seatings highly recommended as you may get mozzie bites if sitting outdoors.
Air flown sashimi from Japan prepared by Japanese or highly qualified chefs. The best of the best
Bentos during lunch hours are great for everyone to start enjoying great Japanese food here. They also serve lunches on weekends!
The chirashi don is to die for....
Lunch sets are reasonably priced for the quality you're getting. Truly one of the best sushi restaurants in Singapore.
I particularly like the swordfish sushi and ozaki beef literally melts in your mouth
chef's choice Aburi Sushi (not on the menu) is amazing. lots of luscious flavors such as truffle oil, yuzu, mentaiko and foie gras
Their lunch bento sets are amazing value- fresh fish and delicious sides. Highly recommended!

Order the set sushi! It is not in the menu! Awesome!!
Sit in front of Andy. Great food and stories.
The best seats are at the counter because you get to see the chef in action. Watching them prepare the food is quite beautiful.
Went here for lunch yesterday and WOAH. The lunch bento was delish. And the salmon nigiri was to die for!!
I love the Chirashi Bento! Can't finish it though. Had a slice of Otoro to start the meal.
On dit que c'est le meilleur japonais en dehors du Japon!
Aburi is a MUST 😋
If you die and go to sushi heaven, you would find yourself in Tatsuya in Singapore!!!
Good bento boxes for lunch!
Absolutely amazing!
The Aburi sushi is pricey, but not to be missed! Flounder, sea bass, kampachi, toro tuna belly, prawn, salmon belly, swordfish belly, and scallop with fois gras! Yum...
A must to try their gyu don
first bottle free. $40++ for every subsequent bottle. BYO not allowed if restaurant already stocks that wine / sake
Omakase! Or just whatever the chefs serve up! Excellent!!
Lunch bento set selections are great! Very fresh ingredients! Ask to be seated at sushi bar cause you'll have the chance to see the skillful chefs preparing sashimi, sushi and other dishes.
Melts in your mouth tuna belly , Omakase is a must have at Tatsuya
Excellent food but pricy. No wonder that outside of it Ferrari and Lamborghini are parking
Double Boiled Soup with Fat Tuna <3
They claim that all fish are imported from the famous fish market tsukiji in Tokyo.  The fish do taste very fresh and yummy!  in in Singapore.
This is rated 1 of the best in Sg. Indeed, no joke!!
Chirashi Lunch Bento :)
Do the omakase. Expensive but amazing sashimi, sushi, and other treats
probably the best top quality lunch sets in town
Service is impeccable , aburi sushi and the sashimi
Excellent sashimi quality. Wagyu is good.
Shocking service, cramped and noisy, bad attitude, waste of time and money unless watching willing but untrained waitresses from 3rd world countries being screamed at by a Japanese chef.
Have lunch here to try it
By far, one of the best Sushi places I've ever been. Great food and amazing staff. Go with the chef's choice. He'll give you his recommendations and all you have to do is ENJOY!
Salmon roe season starts in October. The earlier batch will be more tender. It gets crunchier after the 3rd week..
Best sushi !
Best Japanese restaurant in Singapore. The Simmered Sea Bream Head was amazing. The Sashimi and Sushi worth the visit. 🌟🌟🌟🌟
For the past 8 years, the trademark here is excellent service which is why I always come back.The owner Ronnie Chia takes pride in quality and service.
Bento boxes are a great option for lunch.
Simply the best !!
Go for the lunch bentos, the best way to get to know the restaurant. Dinner will cost much more
Gyu don & their seared sushi ~ extremely gratifying at Tatsuya !!!
The lunchtime Bento set ($30) was included in Time Out’s 2012 best dishes list for Best Sushi.
Хочется обратиться ко всем отечественным любителям суши: раскашельтесь хотя бы на один ужин здесь, чтобы узнать наконец, какими должны быть настоящие японские суси. Отличное место.
Not an intimidating setting. Food is alright but a little too much condiments ie mayonnaise or chilli flakes. Omakase should be live, fresh, 原汁原味。
Amazing Aburi

Sashimi is very fresh!
Very fresh sashimi!!! Yums!!!
Best set lunch in town. Try their premium sashimi too. Better still.. Get tatsuya's omakase dinner set
Gyu don - a must try for the mini bowl ! So gooood !!! Not on the menu, so tell the chef to top with an egg !
Melt-in-your-mouth Fatty Tuna Belly, exquisite assortment of Sushi, punctuated by Foie Gras and caviar, succulent sashimi, perfectly seared Wagyu fillet..this is heaven. Go for Chef's Omakase. Enjoy!
Amazing sushi. And also melt in your mouth wagyu beef and toro sashimi
Joevios in operation!!
kind of on the pricey side but worth the money. the lunch deals are great.
Amazing Omakase!!! Wooo...
Expensive albeit high quality. Bookings almost always a must!
Have to make reservations early if you do not want to seat by the counter.
Can do no wrong with Ronnie and team. LOVE.
Sushi is definitely Salivating & to die for
